###Block: Sandman Abilities
Sand Form	KEY:Sand Form ~ Sandman	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	DESC:As a standard action, a sandman can cause its humanoid form to collapse into a pile of animated sand.  In this form, treat the sandman as if it were a Small earth elemental made out of sand.  The sandman retains its compression and sleep aura abilities when in sand form, but loses its sleep attack and its damage reduction, as its sandy body in this form is much more compact and easier to scatter with solid blows.	SOURCEPAGE:p.236
Sleep		KEY:Sleep ~ Sandman	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:A crature struck by a sandman's slam attack must succeed on a DC %1 Will save or immediately fall asleep, as if affected by a sleep spell (caster level 8th).  There is no limit to the number of Hit Dice a sandman can affect with this ability.|SandmanSleepDC	DEFINE:SandmanSleepDC|0	BONUS:VAR|SandmanSleepDC|10+TL/2+CON	SOURCEPAGE:p.236	BONUS:VAR|SandmanSleepDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Sleep)
Sleep Aura	KEY:Sleep Aura ~ Sandman	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Aura.Supernatural	DESC:A sandman radiates a 20-foot-radius spread that puts creatures to sleep.  Any creature in the area must succeed on a DC %1 Will save or fall asleep, as if affected by a sleep spell (caster level 8th).  There is no limit to the number of Hit Dice a sandman can affect with this ability.  A creature that successfully saves is immune to that sandman's sleep aura for 24 hours.|SandmanSleepAuraDC	DEFINE:SandmanSleepAuraDC|0	BONUS:VAR|SandmanSleepAuraDC|10+TL/2+CON	SOURCEPAGE:p.236	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(20 ft., DC %1)|SandmanSleepAuraDC	BONUS:VAR|SandmanSleepAuraDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Sleep Aura)

###Block: Sard Abilities
Death Throes	KEY:Death Throes ~ Sard	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Defensive.Supernatural	DESC:When a sard dies, its remains explode with a blast of lightning into razor-sharp splinters of wood.  All creatures within 30 feet of a sard when it explodes in this manner take 12d6 points of electricity damage and 12d6 points of piercing damage.  A DC %1 Reflex save halves this damage.|SardDeathThroesDC	DEFINE:SardDeathThroesDC|0	BONUS:VAR|SardDeathThroesDC|10+TL/2+CON	SOURCEPAGE:p.237	BONUS:VAR|SardDeathThroesDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Death Throes)
Electrical Jolt	KEY:Electrical Jolt ~ Sard	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Defensive.Supernatural	DESC:Every time a creature strikes a sard with a metal melee weapon, arcs of electricity deal 1d10 points of damage to the attacker.	SOURCEPAGE:p.237
Planar Acclimation	KEY:Planar Acclimation ~ Sard	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:A sard is always considered to be on its home plane, regardless of what plane it finds itself upon.  It never gains the extraplanar subtype.	SOURCEPAGE:p.237
Poison	KEY:Poison ~ Sard	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	DESC:Thorn - injury; save Fort DC %1; frequency 1/round for 5 rounds; effect 1d2 Dex and 4d6 electricity; cure 2 consecutive saves.|SardPoisonDC	DEFINE:SardPoisonDC|0	BONUS:VAR|SardPoisonDC|10+TL/2+CON	SOURCEPAGE:p.237	BONUS:VAR|SardPoisonDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Poison)
Electric Slam	KEY:Electric Slam ~ Sard	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:A sard's slam attack also deals 4d6 points of electricity damage.	SOURCEPAGE:p.237

###Block: Scarecrow Abilities
Fascinating Gaze	KEY:Fascinating Gaze ~ Scarecrow	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:Target is fascinated, 30 feet, Will DC %1 negates.  Fascination lasts as long as the scarecrow remains within 300 feet of the fascinated creature.  The approach or animation of the scarecrow does not count as an obvious threat to the victim of this particular fascination (although the scarecrow's attack does count as an obvious threat and ends the fascination immediately).  This is a mind-affecting effect.|ScarecrowFascinatingGazeDC	DEFINE:ScarecrowFascinatingGazeDC|0	BONUS:VAR|ScarecrowFascinatingGazeDC|10+TL/2+CHA	SOURCEPAGE:p.238	BONUS:VAR|ScarecrowFascinatingGazeDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Fascinating Gaze)
Fear			KEY:Fear ~ Scarecrow	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:A scarecrow's touch infuses its target with overwhelming waves of fear.  If the victim fails a DC %1 Will sve, she cowers and can take no actions other than attempting a new DC %1 Will save at the end of the following round (and each round thereafter) to end this fear.  A successful first save leaves the victim shaken for 1 round.  This is a mind-affecting fear effect.|ScarecrowFearDC	DEFINE:ScarecrowFearDC|0	BONUS:VAR|ScarecrowFearDC|10+TL/2+CHA	SOURCEPAGE:p.238	BONUS:VAR|ScarecrowFearDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Fear)

###Block: Sceaduinar Abilities
Entropic Flesh	KEY:Entropic Flesh ~ Sceaduinar	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Defensive.Extraordinary	DESC:Any creature that hits a sceaduinar with a melee attack takes 1d6 points of negative energy damage.  Attacking with a weapon that provides reach allows a creature to avoid taking this damage.	SOURCEPAGE:p.239
Entropic Touch	KEY:Entropic Touch ~ Sceaduinar	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	DESC:A sceaduinar's natural attacks can strike incorporeal creatures as if they were ghost touch weapons.  All of a sceaduinar's natural attacks deal +1d6 points of negative energy damage to the target.  This energy does not heal creatures healed by inflict spells.	SOURCEPAGE:p.239
Void Child		KEY:Void Child ~ Sceaduinar		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Defensive.Extraordinary	DESC:Sceaduinars are immune to effects that target souls (such as trap the soul) or require knowledge of a creature's identity (such as scrying).  When one is slain, it cannot be restored to life by magic save by a miracle or wish, or by divine intervention.	SOURCEPAGE:p.239

