###Block: Seugathi Abilities
Aura of Madness	KEY:Aura of Madness ~ Seugathi	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Aura.Supernatural	DESC:Any sane being within 30 feet of a conscious seugathi must make a DC %1 Will save each round or become confused for 1 round.  A creature that fails 5 saves in a row becomes permanently insane, as per the insanity spell.  A seugathi can suppress or activate this aura as a free action.  This is a mind-affecting effect.|SeugathiAuraOfMadnessDC	DEFINE:SeugathiAuraOfMadnessDC|0	BONUS:VAR|SeugathiAuraOfMadnessDC|10+TL/2+CHA	BONUS:VAR|SeugathiAuraOfMadnessDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus(Aura of Madness)	SOURCEPAGE:p.243	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(30 ft.)
Confusion Command	KEY:Confusion Command ~ Seugathi	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:As an immediate action, a seugathi can issue a telepathic command to a confused creature within 30 feet.  This allows the seugathi to pick a result from the confusion behavior table, rather than the confused creature rolling randomly for its actions that round.	SOURCEPAGE:p.243
Item Use		KEY:Item Use ~ Seugathi	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:A seugathi can utilize spell trigger devices as if it were a spellcaster of the appropriate class.  As a free action by touch, it can identify all spell trigger properties an item has.  Use Magic Device is a class skill for seugathis.	CSKILL:Use Magic Device	SOURCEPAGE:p.243
Poison		KEY:Poison ~ Seugathi	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	DESC:Bite - injury; save Fort DC %1; frequency 1/round for 6 rounds; effect 1d2 Wis and deafness; cure 2 consecutive saves.  Deafness persists as long as the ability damage caused by the poison lasts.|SeugathiPoisonDC	DEFINE:SeugathiPoisonDC|0	BONUS:VAR|SeugathiPoisonDC|10+TL/2+CON	BONUS:VAR|SeugathiPoisonDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Poison)
