###Block: Shantak Abilities
Share Defenses	KEY:Share Defenses ~ Shantak	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	DESC:As a free action, a shantak can extend its no breath ability and cold immunity to a single creature touching it.  It can withdraw this protection as a free action.	SOURCEPAGE:p.244
Slippery	KEY:Slippery ~ Shantak	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Defensive.Extraordinary	DESC:A shantak's scales seep slippery slime.  This grants the creature a +8 bonus on all Escape Artist checks and to its CMD against grapples, and imparts a -5 penalty on all Ride checks made by creatures attempting to ride a shantak.	SOURCEPAGE:p.244	BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist|8|TYPE=Racial	BONUS:VAR|CMD_GRAPPLE|8|TYPE=Racial
Starflight	KEY:Starflight ~ Shantak	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	DESC:A shantak can survive in the void of outer space.  It flies through space at an incredible speed.  Although exact travel times vary, a trip within a single solar system should take 3d20 hours, while a trip beyond should take 3d20 days (or more, at the GM's discretion) - provided the shantak knows the way to its destination.	SOURCEPAGE:p.244

###Block: Shining Child Abilities
Blinding Light	KEY:Blinding Light ~ Shining Child	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Aura.Extraordinary	DESC:A shining child can radiate a 60-foot-radius aura of blinding light as a free action.  Creatures within the affected area must succeed on a DC %1 Fortitude save or be permanently blinded.  A creature that successfully saves cannot be affected again by the same shining child's aura for 24 hours.|ShiningChildBlindingLightDC	DEFINE:ShiningChildBlindingLightDC|0	BONUS:VAR|ShiningChildBlindingLightDC|10+TL/2+CON	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(60 feet)	SOURCEPAGE:p.245	BONUS:VAR|ShiningChildBlindingLightDC|2|PREFEAT:1,Ability Focus (Blinding Light)
Burning Touch	KEY:Burning Touch ~ Shining Child	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:A shining child corrupts the positive energy within a living creature into an unnatural burning light.  For the next 5 rounds after a successful touch attack by a shining child, the target takes 2d6 points of fire damage.  The burning light can be "extinguished" by casting darkness or deeper darkness on the target, or by antering an area of natural darkness (not counting the light from the burning target).	SOURCEPAGE:p.245
Radiant Armor	KEY:Radiant Armor ~ Shining Child	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural	DESC:The light that surrounds a shining child grants a deflection bonus to its AC equal to its Charisma bonus.  The bonus is negated as long as the shining child is in the area of effect of a spell with the darkness descriptor that is at least 3rd level.	BONUS:COMBAT|AC|CHA|TYPE=Deflection	SOURCEPAGE:p.245
Searing Ray		KEY:Searing Ray ~ Shining Child	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural	DESC:A shining child's primary attack is a ray of searing light.  This attack has a range of 120 feet and bypasses all damage reduction.  The ray deals double damage to undead.	SOURCEPAGE:p.245

